{
  "texts": [
    "(Wang et al. 2019) proposed a graph attention convolution method capable of adapting to the shape of the target, which is specially designed for the semantic segmentation task of point clouds.",
    "By using a pyramid structure, combining graph attention convolution for local feature extraction, and global graph pooling to reduce the resolution of the point cloud in the feature channel, the method effectively improves the accuracy of point cloud processing.",
    "In solving the point cloud segmentation task, (Chen et al. 2020c) proposed the hierarchical attention pooling graph network (HAPGN), which combines the gated graph attention network (GGAN) and the hierarchical graph pooling (HiGPool).",
    "HAPGN combines the ability of GNNs to capture local structure and relationships with the ability of graph pooling to capture hierarchical information and global structure, effectively compensating for the shortcomings of existing methods in terms of correlation between nodes and their neighborhoods as well as learning local structure information.",
    "To address the challenge of capturing advanced geometric correlations, (Li et al. 2019) proposed the Taylor Gaussian mixture model (TGMM) network (TGNet)."
  ]
}